n: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Christopher Hemmelgarn</a>&nbsp;of Barclays believes revenue stream from cryptocurrency is fickle. Therefore, the analysts were not in favor of assigning a multiple to it, as it has the potential to become an eventual headwind.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Rival&nbsp;<strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"bztwchangezero\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 0.8rem; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(199, 225, 235); border-radius: 0.2rem; display: inline-block; line-height: 20px; white-space: nowrap; font-family: \" open=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 86,=\"\" 139);\"=\"\"><a id=\"bztwchangepercentzero\" class=\"ticker bztwwidgethover\" title=\"AMD\" data-ticker=\"AMD\" href=\"https://benzinga.com/stock/amd#NASDAQ\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.4rem; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12.8px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; display: block; color: rgb(0, 86, 139); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">AMD</a></span>&nbsp;also had a similar tale to tell. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/17/07/9823514/amd-delivers-q2-beat-and-bmo-promptly-downgrades-the-sto\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">company</a>indicated that cryptocurrency demand remains strong, while also suggesting that the demand might not last forever.</p><h3 style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 21px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">What Is Cryptocurrency?</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/0/cryptocurrency/\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Cryptocurrency,&nbsp;</a>as the name suggests, is a form of digital money designed to be secure and anonymous in most cases. It uses a technique called cryptography — a process used to convert legible information into an almost uncrackable code, to help track purchases and transfers.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Giving a simple definition,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blockgeeks.com/guides/what-is-cryptocurrency/\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Blockgeeks&nbsp;</a>says it is just limited entries in a database no one can change without fulfilling specific conditions.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Cryptography is a technique that uses elements of mathematical theory and computer science and was evolved during the World War II to securely transfer data and information. Currently, it is used to secure communications, information and money online.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Cryptocurrencies allow users to make secure payments, without having to go through banks.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Some cryptocurrencies include bitcoin, Bitcoin Cash,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/17/07/9740796/the-history-of-ethereum-in-one-infographic\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Ethereum,&nbsp;</a>DigitalNote, LiteCoin and PotCoin.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Bitcoin has the distinction of being the first cryptocurrency, having been introduced in 2009. Since then, this class of cryptocurrencies mushroomed, with more than 900 currently active.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">See also:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/17/06/9665582/chips-and-cryptocurrencies-a-match-made-in-tech-heaven\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Chips And Cryptocurrencies: A Match Made In Tech Heaven?</a></em></p><h3 style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 21px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">How Cryptocurrencies Work</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">A cryptocurrency runs on a blockchain, which is a shared ledger or document duplicated several times across a network of computers. The updated document is distributed and made available to all holders of the cryptocurrency.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Every single transaction made and the ownership of every single cryptocurrency in circulation is recorded in the blockchain. The blockchain is run by miners, who use powerful computers that tally the transactions. Their function is to update each time a transaction is made and also ensure the authenticity of information, thereby ascertaining that each transaction is secure and is processed properly and safely.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">As payment for their services, miners are paid physically minted cryptocurrency as fees by vendors or merchants of each transaction.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">The value of the cryptocurrency fluctuates based on demand and supply, although there is no fixed value for it. Buyers and sellers agree on a value, which is fair and is based on the value of the cryptocurrency trading elsewhere.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Since there is no intermediary like bank involved in the transaction, as it is a peer-to-peer transaction, the transaction fee that is associated with credit cards is eliminated. The identity of the buyer and seller are not revealed. However, each and every transaction is made public to all the people in the blockchain network.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">One can acquire a cryptocurrency through exchanges found online or trade it for traditional currencies.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Assume X wants to buy an item valued at $10,000 and he realizes that the seller Y accepts cryptocurrency, say bitcoin, as a form of payment. X scouts around to find the prevailing exchange rate, say $1,000 per currency. X gets Y\'s public Bitcoin address from Y\'s website, although both parties remain anonymous to each other.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">X can now instruct his Bitcoin client or the software installed on his computer to transfer 10 bitcoins from his wallet to Y\'s address. X\'s Bitcoin client will electronically sign the transaction request with his private key known only to him. X\'s public key, which is a public information, can be used for verifying the information.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">When X\'s transaction is broadcast to the Bitcoin network, it would be verified in a few minutes by miners. The 10 bitcoins will now be transferred to Y\'s address.</p><h3 style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 21px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Mining</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Cryptocurrency mining includes two functions, namely: adding transactions to the blockchain (securing and verifying) and also releasing new currency. Individual blocks added by miners should contain a proof-of-work, or PoW.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Mining needs a computer and a special program, which helps miners compete with their peers in solving complicated mathematical problems. This would need huge computer resources. In regular intervals, miners would attempt to solve a block having the transaction data using cryptographic hash functions.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/security/ensuring-data-integrity-with-hash-codes\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Hash value&nbsp;</a>is a numeric value of fixed length that uniquely identifies data. Miners use their computer to zero in on a hash value less than the target and whoever is the first to crack it would be considered as the one who mined the block and is eligible to get a rewarded.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">The reward for mining a block is now 12.5 bitcoins.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Earlier, only cryptography enthusiasts served as miners. However, as cryptocurrencies gained in popularity and increased in value, mining is now considered a lucrative business. Consequently, several people and enterprises have started investing in warehouses and hardware.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">As enterprises jumped into the fray, unable to compete, bitcoin miners have begun to join open pools, combining resources to effectively compete.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Bank of New York Mellon Corp&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"bztwnegative\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 0.8rem; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 188, 169); border-radius: 0.2rem; display: inline-block; line-height: 20px; white-space: nowrap; font-family: \" open=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(178,=\"\" 34,=\"\" 34);\"=\"\"><a id=\"bztwredarrow\" class=\"ticker bztwwidgethover\" title=\"BK\" data-ticker=\"BK\" href=\"https://benzinga.com/stock/bk#NYSE\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.4rem; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12.8px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; display: block; color: rgb(178, 34, 34); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\"><span class=\"arrow-down--tw\" style=\"margin: 0px 3px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 9px 5px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(178, 34, 34); border-right-color: transparent; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: transparent; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;\"></span>BK 0.42%</a></span>&nbsp;has been running an internal blockchain platform for U.S. Treasury bond settlements since early 2016, a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.marketwatch.com/story/bitcoin-needs-government-regulation-to-rise-further-morgan-stanley-says-2017-06-13\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Marketwatch&nbsp;</a>report quoting Morgan Stanley said. The private nature of the platform has kept it out of the regulatory purview. Once the bank decides to roll it out to clients and use it commercially, regulatory oversight might come into the picture.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">A complete mining kit consists of graphics cards, a processor, power supply, memory, cabling and a fan, which would cost between $2,400 and $3,800 on&nbsp;<strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Amazon.com, Inc.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"bztwnegative\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 0.8rem; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 188, 169); border-radius: 0.2rem; display: inline-block; line-height: 20px; white-space: nowrap; font-family: \" open=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(178,=\"\" 34,=\"\" 34);\"=\"\"><a id=\"bztwredarrow\" class=\"ticker bztwwidgethover\" title=\"AMZN\" data-ticker=\"AMZN\" href=\"https://benzinga.com/stock/amzn#NASDAQ\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.4rem; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12.8px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; display: block; color: rgb(178, 34, 34); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\"><span class=\"arrow-down--tw\" style=\"margin: 0px 3px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 9px 5px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(178, 34, 34); border-right-color: transparent; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: transparent; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;\"></span>AMZN 0.34%</a></span>, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-06-08/these-companies-stand-to-gain-the-most-amid-digital-coin-rush\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">Bloomberg.</a></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">The top three mining hardware, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://99bitcoins.com/2016-bitcoin-mining-hardware-comparison/\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(35, 109, 201); cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(252, 215, 0);\">99bitcoins.com,&nbsp;</a>are Avalon6, AntMiner S7 and AntMiner S9.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Given that existing GPUs aren\'t powerful enough, now miners are flocking to application-specific integrated circuits, or ASICs. To circumvent this shortcoming, Nvidia and AMD are said to be working on GPUs, which could be used specifically for the purpose.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">The two companies who are dominant in consumer-grade mining hardware are Canaan and Bitmain. Bitmain, based in Beijing, does mining as well as manufactures mining hardware.</p><h3 style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 21px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Mining Pools And Their Share Of Mining</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><img alt=\"pools.png\" height=\"1124\" src=\"https://cdn2.benzinga.com/files/u101977/pools.png\" width=\"1386\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; max-width: 685px;\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Source: Block Chain</em></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Mining pools are concentrated in China, which boasts of 81 percent of the network hash rate.</p><h3 style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 21px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Why Mining Chips Are A Fickle Revenue Stream</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">For companies such as AMD and Nvidia, which have dominant positions in the gaming chip market, a focus away from their core business may not be a prudent course of action.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">As seen, these companies may have to bring out new GPUs designed exclusively for this purpose to pose a real threat to the ASIC chips, which are predominantly manufactured by the Chinese, who are notorious for their low-cost market positioning. How viable is the spend on such exclusive chips is a moot point.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \" helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" opensans,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">Additionally, national governments and exchanges are mulling over regulation of the whole realm of cryptocurrencies. Japan has recently introduced legislation to protect users after Tokyo-based Bitcoin exchange Mt Gox collapsed in 2014. Similarly, introducing taxation such as capital gains tax on Bitcoin sales may also impede the cryptocurrency industry.</p>', 'publish', '2018-06-16 04:37:51', 0),
(8, 'Admin', '2018-06-16 10:13:03', 'What is a Blog? – The Definition of Blog, Blogging, and Blogger', 'what-is-a-blog-the-definition-of-blog-blogging-and-blogger', 'What_is_a_1529143983.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">Do you know what blogs are? If you don’t, then you’ve come to the right place. In the beginning, a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://firstsiteguide.com/glossary/blog/\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">blog</a>&nbsp;was more of a personal diary that people shared online, and it goes back to 1994. On this online journal, you could talk about your daily life or share things you do. But, people saw an opportunity to communicate any information in a new way. So began the beautiful world of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://firstsiteguide.com/learn-blogging/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">blogging</a>.</p>&nbsp;<h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-size: 2rem;\">What is a Blog?</h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-size: 1.75rem;\">Definition of blog</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">A blog (shortening of “weblog”) is an online journal or informational website displaying information in the reverse chronological order, with latest posts appearing first. It is a platform where a writer or even a group of writers share their views on an individual subject.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-size: 1.75rem;\">Blog structure</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">The appearance of blogs changed over time, and nowadays blogs include different items. But, most blogs include some standard features and structure. Here are common features that typical blog will include:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><li><a href=\"https://firstsiteguide.com/glossary/header/\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Header</a>&nbsp;with the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://firstsiteguide.com/glossary/menu/\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">menu</a>&nbsp;or navigation bar</li><li>Main content area with highlighted or latest blog posts</li><li>Sidebar with social profiles, favorite content, or call-to-action</li><li>Footer with relevant links like a disclaimer, privacy policy, contact page, etc.</li></ul>', 'publish', '2018-06-16 10:13:03', 0),
(9, 'Admin', '2018-06-16 10:15:14', 'Changed Title', 'changed-title-1530005983', 'What_is_a_1529144114.png', '<p>Hey there, today we are going to learn about <a href=\"somewhwere.com\" title=\"something\" target=\"_blank\">something</a>.</p><ul><li>shopping</li><li>Bathing</li><li>Kitchen</li><li>Tutorial</li></ul><p>That\'s is . see you next time.</p><p><em><strong>bye bye</strong></em></p>', 'publish', '2018-06-26 09:39:43', 0),
