\narithmetic expression where an operator is placed in between its two operands\r\nthat means (operand1 operator operand2&gt;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n150%\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%;\">Eg. A+b, a-b, a/b, a%b etc.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"margin-left:72.0pt;text-indent:-72.0pt;mso-list:l3 level5 lfo9\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong>2.2.1.2.2<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong>Prefix expression<o:p></o:p></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n150%\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%;\">In prefix notation an operator is placed\r\nbefore its two operands. It is also known as Polish notation. That means\r\n&lt;operator operand1 operand2&gt;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n150%\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%;\">Eg. +ab, -ab, /ab, %ab etc.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"margin-left:72.0pt;text-indent:-72.0pt;mso-list:l3 level5 lfo9\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong>2.2.1.2.3<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp